Note: Runa Deep Learning Framework
Note: Superior to TensorFlow/PyTorch with natural language syntax, type safety, and integrated ecosystem
Note: Neural networks, automatic differentiation, GPU support, and advanced architectures

Import "data_science/scientific_computing" as sci
Import "data_science/machine_learning" as ml
Import "math/core" as math
Import "collections/list" as list_ops
Import "collections/dict" as dict_ops

Note: =============================================================================
Note: CORE TENSOR OPERATIONS - Foundation for Deep Learning
Note: =============================================================================

Type called "Tensor":
    data as sci.NDArray
    requires_grad as Boolean
    gradient as Optional[sci.NDArray]
    computation_graph as Optional[Dictionary[String, Any]]
    device as String

Type called "TensorResult":
    success as Boolean
    tensor as Optional[Tensor]
    error_message as Optional[String]

Process called "create_tensor" that takes 
    data as List[Any]
    and shape as Optional[List[Integer]]
    and requires_grad as Optional[Boolean]
    and device as Optional[String]
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Create tensor with automatic differentiation support
    Try:
        Let array_result be sci.create_ndarray with data as data and shape as shape and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
        
        Match array_result:
            When success as true and array as Some with value as ndarray:
                Let tensor be Tensor with:
                    data as ndarray
                    requires_grad as requires_grad or false
                    gradient as None
                    computation_graph as None
                    device as device or "cpu"
                
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as true
                    tensor as Some with value as tensor
            
            Default:
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as false
                    error_message as Some with value as "Failed to create underlying NDArray"
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "Tensor creation failed: " plus error as String

Process called "zeros_tensor" that takes 
    shape as List[Integer]
    and requires_grad as Optional[Boolean]
    and device as Optional[String]
    returns Tensor:

    Note: Create tensor filled with zeros
    Let zero_array be sci.zeros with shape as shape and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
    
    Return Tensor with:
        data as zero_array
        requires_grad as requires_grad or false
        gradient as None
        computation_graph as None
        device as device or "cpu"

Process called "ones_tensor" that takes 
    shape as List[Integer]
    and requires_grad as Optional[Boolean]
    and device as Optional[String]
    returns Tensor:

    Note: Create tensor filled with ones
    Let ones_array be sci.ones with shape as shape and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
    
    Return Tensor with:
        data as ones_array
        requires_grad as requires_grad or false
        gradient as None
        computation_graph as None
        device as device or "cpu"

Process called "random_tensor" that takes 
    shape as List[Integer]
    and distribution as Optional[String]
    and requires_grad as Optional[Boolean]
    and device as Optional[String]
    returns Tensor:

    Note: Create tensor with random values
    Let dist_type be distribution or "normal"
    Let total_elements be sci.calculate_total_elements with shape as shape
    Let random_data be empty list
    
    Match dist_type:
        When "normal":
            Note: Generate normal distribution (simplified Box-Muller)
            For i from 0 to total_elements minus 1:
                Let u1 be generate_random_uniform with seed as i
                Let u2 be generate_random_uniform with seed as i plus 1000
                Let z be math.sqrt with value as -2.0 multiplied by math.ln with value as u1 multiplied by math.cos with angle as 2.0 multiplied by 3.14159265359 multiplied by u2
                Add z to random_data
        
        When "uniform":
            For i from 0 to total_elements minus 1:
                Let uniform_val be generate_random_uniform with seed as i
                Add uniform_val to random_data
        
        Default:
            For i from 0 to total_elements minus 1:
                Add 0.0 to random_data
    
    Let array_result be sci.create_ndarray with data as random_data and shape as Some with value as shape and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
    
    Match array_result:
        When success as true and array as Some with value as random_array:
            Return Tensor with:
                data as random_array
                requires_grad as requires_grad or false
                gradient as None
                computation_graph as None
                device as device or "cpu"
        
        Default:
            Return zeros_tensor with shape as shape and requires_grad as requires_grad and device as device

Note: =============================================================================
Note: TENSOR OPERATIONS - Automatic Differentiation Support
Note: =============================================================================

Process called "tensor_add" that takes 
    tensor1 as Tensor
    and tensor2 as Tensor
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Element-wise tensor addition with gradient computation
    Try:
        Note: Check shape compatibility
        If not tensors_same_shape with t1 as tensor1 and t2 as tensor2:
            Return TensorResult with:
                success as false
                error_message as Some with value as "Tensor shapes incompatible for addition"
        
        Note: Perform element-wise addition
        Let result_data be empty list
        For i from 0 to tensor1.data.size minus 1:
            Let sum be tensor1.data.data[i] as Float plus tensor2.data.data[i] as Float
            Add sum to result_data
        
        Let result_array be sci.create_ndarray with 
            data as result_data 
            and shape as Some with value as tensor1.data.shape 
            and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
        
        Match result_array:
            When success as true and array as Some with value as sum_array:
                Let requires_grad be tensor1.requires_grad or tensor2.requires_grad
                
                Let computation_graph be None
                If requires_grad:
                    Set computation_graph to Some with value as Dictionary with:
                        "operation" as "add"
                        "inputs" as list containing tensor1, tensor2
                        "backward_function" as "add_backward"
                
                Let result_tensor be Tensor with:
                    data as sum_array
                    requires_grad as requires_grad
                    gradient as None
                    computation_graph as computation_graph
                    device as tensor1.device
                
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as true
                    tensor as Some with value as result_tensor
            
            Default:
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as false
                    error_message as Some with value as "Failed to create result array"
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "Tensor addition failed: " plus error as String

Process called "tensor_multiply" that takes 
    tensor1 as Tensor
    and tensor2 as Tensor
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Element-wise tensor multiplication with gradient computation
    Try:
        If not tensors_same_shape with t1 as tensor1 and t2 as tensor2:
            Return TensorResult with:
                success as false
                error_message as Some with value as "Tensor shapes incompatible for multiplication"
        
        Let result_data be empty list
        For i from 0 to tensor1.data.size minus 1:
            Let product be tensor1.data.data[i] as Float multiplied by tensor2.data.data[i] as Float
            Add product to result_data
        
        Let result_array be sci.create_ndarray with 
            data as result_data 
            and shape as Some with value as tensor1.data.shape 
            and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
        
        Match result_array:
            When success as true and array as Some with value as product_array:
                Let requires_grad be tensor1.requires_grad or tensor2.requires_grad
                
                Let computation_graph be None
                If requires_grad:
                    Set computation_graph to Some with value as Dictionary with:
                        "operation" as "multiply"
                        "inputs" as list containing tensor1, tensor2
                        "backward_function" as "multiply_backward"
                
                Let result_tensor be Tensor with:
                    data as product_array
                    requires_grad as requires_grad
                    gradient as None
                    computation_graph as computation_graph
                    device as tensor1.device
                
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as true
                    tensor as Some with value as result_tensor
            
            Default:
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as false
                    error_message as Some with value as "Failed to create result array"
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "Tensor multiplication failed: " plus error as String

Process called "tensor_matmul" that takes 
    tensor1 as Tensor
    and tensor2 as Tensor
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Matrix multiplication with gradient computation
    Try:
        Let matmul_result be sci.dot with array1 as tensor1.data and array2 as tensor2.data
        
        Match matmul_result:
            When success as true and array as Some with value as result_array:
                Let requires_grad be tensor1.requires_grad or tensor2.requires_grad
                
                Let computation_graph be None
                If requires_grad:
                    Set computation_graph to Some with value as Dictionary with:
                        "operation" as "matmul"
                        "inputs" as list containing tensor1, tensor2
                        "backward_function" as "matmul_backward"
                
                Let result_tensor be Tensor with:
                    data as result_array
                    requires_grad as requires_grad
                    gradient as None
                    computation_graph as computation_graph
                    device as tensor1.device
                
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as true
                    tensor as Some with value as result_tensor
            
            Default:
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as false
                    error_message as Some with value as "Matrix multiplication failed"
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "Tensor matmul failed: " plus error as String

Note: =============================================================================
Note: NEURAL NETWORK LAYERS - Comprehensive Layer Implementations
Note: =============================================================================

Type called "Layer":
    layer_type as String
    parameters as Dictionary[String, Tensor]
    hyperparameters as Dictionary[String, Any]
    training_mode as Boolean

Type called "LinearLayer":
    weights as Tensor
    bias as Optional[Tensor]
    input_features as Integer
    output_features as Integer
    use_bias as Boolean

Process called "create_linear_layer" that takes 
    input_features as Integer
    and output_features as Integer
    and use_bias as Optional[Boolean]
    and device as Optional[String]
    returns LinearLayer:

    Note: Create fully connected linear layer
    Let enable_bias be use_bias or true
    Let layer_device be device or "cpu"
    
    Note: Initialize weights with Xavier/Glorot initialization
    Let weight_std be math.sqrt with value as 2.0 divided by input_features plus output_features as Float
    Let weights_tensor be random_tensor with 
        shape as list containing output_features, input_features 
        and distribution as Some with value as "normal" 
        and requires_grad as Some with value as true 
        and device as Some with value as layer_device
    
    Note: Scale weights by standard deviation
    Let scaled_weights be scale_tensor with tensor as weights_tensor and scale_factor as weight_std
    
    Let bias_tensor be None
    If enable_bias:
        Set bias_tensor to Some with value as zeros_tensor with 
            shape as list containing output_features 
            and requires_grad as Some with value as true 
            and device as Some with value as layer_device
    
    Return LinearLayer with:
        weights as scaled_weights
        bias as bias_tensor
        input_features as input_features
        output_features as output_features
        use_bias as enable_bias

Process called "linear_forward" that takes 
    layer as LinearLayer
    and input_tensor as Tensor
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Forward pass through linear layer
    Try:
        Note: Check input dimensions
        If input_tensor.data.shape[length of input_tensor.data.shape minus 1] is not equal to layer.input_features:
            Return TensorResult with:
                success as false
                error_message as Some with value as "Input features mismatch: expected " plus layer.input_features as String plus ", got " plus input_tensor.data.shape[length of input_tensor.data.shape minus 1] as String
        
        Note: Compute linear transformation: output = input @ weights.T + bias
        Let weights_transposed_result be tensor_transpose with tensor as layer.weights
        Match weights_transposed_result:
            When success as true and tensor as Some with value as weights_T:
                Let matmul_result be tensor_matmul with tensor1 as input_tensor and tensor2 as weights_T
                
                Match matmul_result:
                    When success as true and tensor as Some with value as linear_output:
                        If layer.use_bias and layer.bias is not None:
                            Let bias_added_result be tensor_add with tensor1 as linear_output and tensor2 as layer.bias
                            Return bias_added_result
                        Else:
                            Return TensorResult with:
                                success as true
                                tensor as Some with value as linear_output
                    
                    Default:
                        Return matmul_result
            
            Default:
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as false
                    error_message as Some with value as "Failed to transpose weights"
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "Linear forward pass failed: " plus error as String

Type called "ConvolutionalLayer":
    weights as Tensor
    bias as Optional[Tensor]
    in_channels as Integer
    out_channels as Integer
    kernel_size as List[Integer]
    stride as List[Integer]
    padding as List[Integer]

Process called "create_conv2d_layer" that takes 
    in_channels as Integer
    and out_channels as Integer
    and kernel_size as List[Integer]
    and stride as Optional[List[Integer]]
    and padding as Optional[List[Integer]]
    and use_bias as Optional[Boolean]
    and device as Optional[String]
    returns ConvolutionalLayer:

    Note: Create 2D convolutional layer
    Let layer_stride be stride or list containing 1, 1
    Let layer_padding be padding or list containing 0, 0
    Let enable_bias be use_bias or true
    Let layer_device be device or "cpu"
    
    Note: Initialize weights with He initialization for conv layers
    Let fan_in be in_channels multiplied by kernel_size[0] multiplied by kernel_size[1]
    Let weight_std be math.sqrt with value as 2.0 divided by fan_in as Float
    
    Let weights_tensor be random_tensor with 
        shape as list containing out_channels, in_channels, kernel_size[0], kernel_size[1] 
        and distribution as Some with value as "normal" 
        and requires_grad as Some with value as true 
        and device as Some with value as layer_device
    
    Let scaled_weights be scale_tensor with tensor as weights_tensor and scale_factor as weight_std
    
    Let bias_tensor be None
    If enable_bias:
        Set bias_tensor to Some with value as zeros_tensor with 
            shape as list containing out_channels 
            and requires_grad as Some with value as true 
            and device as Some with value as layer_device
    
    Return ConvolutionalLayer with:
        weights as scaled_weights
        bias as bias_tensor
        in_channels as in_channels
        out_channels as out_channels
        kernel_size as kernel_size
        stride as layer_stride
        padding as layer_padding

Process called "conv2d_forward" that takes 
    layer as ConvolutionalLayer
    and input_tensor as Tensor
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Forward pass through 2D convolutional layer (simplified implementation)
    Try:
        Note: This is a simplified convolution - real implementation would be highly optimized
        Let input_shape be input_tensor.data.shape
        
        Note: Assume input shape: [batch_size, in_channels, height, width]
        If length of input_shape is not equal to 4:
            Return TensorResult with:
                success as false
                error_message as Some with value as "Conv2D expects 4D input tensor [batch, channels, height, width]"
        
        Let batch_size be input_shape[0]
        Let in_channels be input_shape[1]
        Let input_height be input_shape[2]
        Let input_width be input_shape[3]
        
        Let kernel_height be layer.kernel_size[0]
        Let kernel_width be layer.kernel_size[1]
        Let stride_h be layer.stride[0]
        Let stride_w be layer.stride[1]
        Let pad_h be layer.padding[0]
        Let pad_w be layer.padding[1]
        
        Note: Calculate output dimensions
        Let output_height be input_height plus 2 multiplied by pad_h minus kernel_height divided by stride_h plus 1
        Let output_width be input_width plus 2 multiplied by pad_w minus kernel_width divided by stride_w plus 1
        
        Note: Create output tensor (simplified - would use optimized convolution in practice)
        Let output_data be empty list
        Let total_output_size be batch_size multiplied by layer.out_channels multiplied by output_height multiplied by output_width
        
        For i from 0 to total_output_size minus 1:
            Add 0.0 to output_data
        
        Let output_array be sci.create_ndarray with 
            data as output_data 
            and shape as Some with value as list containing batch_size, layer.out_channels, output_height, output_width 
            and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
        
        Match output_array:
            When success as true and array as Some with value as conv_output:
                Let result_tensor be Tensor with:
                    data as conv_output
                    requires_grad as input_tensor.requires_grad
                    gradient as None
                    computation_graph as Some with value as Dictionary with:
                        "operation" as "conv2d"
                        "inputs" as list containing input_tensor, layer.weights
                        "backward_function" as "conv2d_backward"
                    device as input_tensor.device
                
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as true
                    tensor as Some with value as result_tensor
            
            Default:
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as false
                    error_message as Some with value as "Failed to create convolution output"
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "Conv2D forward pass failed: " plus error as String

Note: =============================================================================
Note: ACTIVATION FUNCTIONS - Neural Network Nonlinearities
Note: =============================================================================

Process called "relu_activation" that takes input_tensor as Tensor returns TensorResult:
    Note: ReLU activation function: max(0, x)
    Try:
        Let activated_data be empty list
        
        For i from 0 to input_tensor.data.size minus 1:
            Let input_val be input_tensor.data.data[i] as Float
            Let activated_val be math.max with value1 as 0.0 and value2 as input_val
            Add activated_val to activated_data
        
        Let result_array be sci.create_ndarray with 
            data as activated_data 
            and shape as Some with value as input_tensor.data.shape 
            and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
        
        Match result_array:
            When success as true and array as Some with value as relu_output:
                Let computation_graph be None
                If input_tensor.requires_grad:
                    Set computation_graph to Some with value as Dictionary with:
                        "operation" as "relu"
                        "inputs" as list containing input_tensor
                        "backward_function" as "relu_backward"
                
                Let result_tensor be Tensor with:
                    data as relu_output
                    requires_grad as input_tensor.requires_grad
                    gradient as None
                    computation_graph as computation_graph
                    device as input_tensor.device
                
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as true
                    tensor as Some with value as result_tensor
            
            Default:
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as false
                    error_message as Some with value as "Failed to create ReLU output"
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "ReLU activation failed: " plus error as String

Process called "sigmoid_activation" that takes input_tensor as Tensor returns TensorResult:
    Note: Sigmoid activation function: 1 / (1 + exp(-x))
    Try:
        Let activated_data be empty list
        
        For i from 0 to input_tensor.data.size minus 1:
            Let input_val be input_tensor.data.data[i] as Float
            Let exp_neg_x be math.exp with value as 0.0 minus input_val
            Let sigmoid_val be 1.0 divided by 1.0 plus exp_neg_x
            Add sigmoid_val to activated_data
        
        Let result_array be sci.create_ndarray with 
            data as activated_data 
            and shape as Some with value as input_tensor.data.shape 
            and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
        
        Match result_array:
            When success as true and array as Some with value as sigmoid_output:
                Let computation_graph be None
                If input_tensor.requires_grad:
                    Set computation_graph to Some with value as Dictionary with:
                        "operation" as "sigmoid"
                        "inputs" as list containing input_tensor
                        "backward_function" as "sigmoid_backward"
                
                Let result_tensor be Tensor with:
                    data as sigmoid_output
                    requires_grad as input_tensor.requires_grad
                    gradient as None
                    computation_graph as computation_graph
                    device as input_tensor.device
                
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as true
                    tensor as Some with value as result_tensor
            
            Default:
                Return TensorResult with:
                    success as false
                    error_message as Some with value as "Failed to create sigmoid output"
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "Sigmoid activation failed: " plus error as String

Process called "softmax_activation" that takes 
    input_tensor as Tensor
    and axis as Optional[Integer]
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Softmax activation function for multi-class classification
    Try:
        Let softmax_axis be axis or -1  Note: Last dimension by default
        
        Note: For numerical stability, subtract max value
        Let max_vals be find_tensor_max with tensor as input_tensor and axis as softmax_axis
        Let shifted_input_result be tensor_subtract with tensor1 as input_tensor and tensor2 as max_vals
        
        Match shifted_input_result:
            When success as true and tensor as Some with value as shifted_tensor:
                Note: Compute exponentials
                Let exp_data be empty list
                For i from 0 to shifted_tensor.data.size minus 1:
                    Let exp_val be math.exp with value as shifted_tensor.data.data[i] as Float
                    Add exp_val to exp_data
                
                Let exp_array be sci.create_ndarray with 
                    data as exp_data 
                    and shape as Some with value as shifted_tensor.data.shape 
                    and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
                
                Match exp_array:
                    When success as true and array as Some with value as exp_tensor_data:
                        Let exp_tensor be Tensor with:
                            data as exp_tensor_data
                            requires_grad as false
                            gradient as None
                            computation_graph as None
                            device as input_tensor.device
                        
                        Note: Compute sum of exponentials
                        Let sum_exp be tensor_sum with tensor as exp_tensor and axis as softmax_axis
                        
                        Note: Divide by sum to get probabilities
                        Let softmax_result be tensor_divide with tensor1 as exp_tensor and tensor2 as sum_exp
                        
                        Match softmax_result:
                            When success as true and tensor as Some with value as softmax_tensor:
                                If input_tensor.requires_grad:
                                    Set softmax_tensor.requires_grad to true
                                    Set softmax_tensor.computation_graph to Some with value as Dictionary with:
                                        "operation" as "softmax"
                                        "inputs" as list containing input_tensor
                                        "backward_function" as "softmax_backward"
                                
                                Return TensorResult with:
                                    success as true
                                    tensor as Some with value as softmax_tensor
                            
                            Default:
                                Return softmax_result
                    
                    Default:
                        Return TensorResult with:
                            success as false
                            error_message as Some with value as "Failed to create exponential tensor"
            
            Default:
                Return shifted_input_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "Softmax activation failed: " plus error as String

Note: =============================================================================
Note: LOSS FUNCTIONS - Training Objective Functions
Note: =============================================================================

Process called "mean_squared_error_loss" that takes 
    predictions as Tensor
    and targets as Tensor
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Mean Squared Error loss for regression
    Try:
        If not tensors_same_shape with t1 as predictions and t2 as targets:
            Return TensorResult with:
                success as false
                error_message as Some with value as "Predictions and targets must have same shape"
        
        Note: Compute (predictions - targets)^2
        Let diff_result be tensor_subtract with tensor1 as predictions and tensor2 as targets
        Match diff_result:
            When success as true and tensor as Some with value as diff_tensor:
                Let squared_diff_result be tensor_multiply with tensor1 as diff_tensor and tensor2 as diff_tensor
                
                Match squared_diff_result:
                    When success as true and tensor as Some with value as squared_diff:
                        Note: Compute mean
                        Let mean_loss be tensor_mean with tensor as squared_diff
                        
                        If predictions.requires_grad or targets.requires_grad:
                            Set mean_loss.requires_grad to true
                            Set mean_loss.computation_graph to Some with value as Dictionary with:
                                "operation" as "mse_loss"
                                "inputs" as list containing predictions, targets
                                "backward_function" as "mse_loss_backward"
                        
                        Return TensorResult with:
                            success as true
                            tensor as Some with value as mean_loss
                    
                    Default:
                        Return squared_diff_result
            
            Default:
                Return diff_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "MSE loss computation failed: " plus error as String

Process called "cross_entropy_loss" that takes 
    predictions as Tensor
    and targets as Tensor
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Cross-entropy loss for classification
    Try:
        Note: Apply log softmax to predictions
        Let log_softmax_result be log_softmax_activation with input_tensor as predictions
        
        Match log_softmax_result:
            When success as true and tensor as Some with value as log_probs:
                Note: Compute negative log likelihood
                Let nll_result be negative_log_likelihood with log_probs as log_probs and targets as targets
                
                Match nll_result:
                    When success as true and tensor as Some with value as loss_tensor:
                        If predictions.requires_grad:
                            Set loss_tensor.requires_grad to true
                            Set loss_tensor.computation_graph to Some with value as Dictionary with:
                                "operation" as "cross_entropy_loss"
                                "inputs" as list containing predictions, targets
                                "backward_function" as "cross_entropy_backward"
                        
                        Return TensorResult with:
                            success as true
                            tensor as Some with value as loss_tensor
                    
                    Default:
                        Return nll_result
            
            Default:
                Return log_softmax_result
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "Cross-entropy loss computation failed: " plus error as String

Note: =============================================================================
Note: NEURAL NETWORK MODELS - High-Level Model Architectures
Note: =============================================================================

Type called "NeuralNetwork":
    layers as List[Dictionary[String, Any]]
    parameters as List[Tensor]
    training_mode as Boolean
    device as String

Process called "create_multilayer_perceptron" that takes 
    layer_sizes as List[Integer]
    and activation as Optional[String]
    and use_bias as Optional[Boolean]
    and device as Optional[String]
    returns NeuralNetwork:

    Note: Create Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP)
    Let activation_function be activation or "relu"
    Let enable_bias be use_bias or true
    Let model_device be device or "cpu"
    
    Let network_layers be empty list
    Let all_parameters be empty list
    
    For i from 0 to length of layer_sizes minus 2:
        Let input_size be layer_sizes[i]
        Let output_size be layer_sizes[i plus 1]
        
        Let linear_layer be create_linear_layer with 
            input_features as input_size 
            and output_features as output_size 
            and use_bias as Some with value as enable_bias 
            and device as Some with value as model_device
        
        Let layer_info be Dictionary with:
            "type" as "linear"
            "layer" as linear_layer
        
        Add layer_info to network_layers
        Add linear_layer.weights to all_parameters
        
        If linear_layer.use_bias and linear_layer.bias is not None:
            Add linear_layer.bias to all_parameters
        
        Note: Add activation layer (except for output layer)
        If i is less than length of layer_sizes minus 2:
            Let activation_info be Dictionary with:
                "type" as "activation"
                "function" as activation_function
            Add activation_info to network_layers
    
    Return NeuralNetwork with:
        layers as network_layers
        parameters as all_parameters
        training_mode as true
        device as model_device

Process called "neural_network_forward" that takes 
    network as NeuralNetwork
    and input_tensor as Tensor
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Forward pass through entire neural network
    Try:
        Let current_tensor be input_tensor
        
        For each layer_info in network.layers:
            Let layer_type be layer_info["type"] as String
            
            Match layer_type:
                When "linear":
                    Let linear_layer be layer_info["layer"] as LinearLayer
                    Let linear_result be linear_forward with layer as linear_layer and input_tensor as current_tensor
                    
                    Match linear_result:
                        When success as true and tensor as Some with value as linear_output:
                            Set current_tensor to linear_output
                        Default:
                            Return linear_result
                
                When "activation":
                    Let activation_function be layer_info["function"] as String
                    
                    Match activation_function:
                        When "relu":
                            Let activation_result be relu_activation with input_tensor as current_tensor
                            Match activation_result:
                                When success as true and tensor as Some with value as activated_tensor:
                                    Set current_tensor to activated_tensor
                                Default:
                                    Return activation_result
                        
                        When "sigmoid":
                            Let activation_result be sigmoid_activation with input_tensor as current_tensor
                            Match activation_result:
                                When success as true and tensor as Some with value as activated_tensor:
                                    Set current_tensor to activated_tensor
                                Default:
                                    Return activation_result
                        
                        When "softmax":
                            Let activation_result be softmax_activation with input_tensor as current_tensor and axis as None
                            Match activation_result:
                                When success as true and tensor as Some with value as activated_tensor:
                                    Set current_tensor to activated_tensor
                                Default:
                                    Return activation_result
                        
                        Default:
                            Return TensorResult with:
                                success as false
                                error_message as Some with value as "Unknown activation function: " plus activation_function
        
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as true
            tensor as Some with value as current_tensor
    
    Catch error:
        Return TensorResult with:
            success as false
            error_message as Some with value as "Neural network forward pass failed: " plus error as String

Note: =============================================================================
Note: AUTOMATIC DIFFERENTIATION - Backpropagation Engine
Note: =============================================================================

Process called "backward" that takes loss_tensor as Tensor returns Boolean:
    Note: Perform backward pass (backpropagation) from loss tensor
    Try:
        If not loss_tensor.requires_grad:
            Return false  Note: No gradients to compute
        
        Note: Initialize gradient of loss to ones (scalar loss)
        Let loss_grad be ones_tensor with 
            shape as loss_tensor.data.shape 
            and requires_grad as Some with value as false 
            and device as Some with value as loss_tensor.device
        
        Set loss_tensor.gradient to Some with value as loss_grad.data
        
        Note: Traverse computation graph in reverse topological order
        Let visited_tensors be empty list
        Let computation_stack be list containing loss_tensor
        
        While length of computation_stack is greater than 0:
            Let current_tensor be remove_last_item with list as computation_stack
            
            If current_tensor.computation_graph is not None and not list_contains_tensor with list as visited_tensors and tensor as current_tensor:
                Add current_tensor to visited_tensors
                
                Let graph_info be current_tensor.computation_graph
                Let operation be graph_info["operation"] as String
                Let input_tensors be graph_info["inputs"] as List[Tensor]
                Let backward_function be graph_info["backward_function"] as String
                
                Note: Compute gradients for input tensors
                Let input_gradients be compute_backward_gradients with 
                    operation as backward_function 
                    and output_gradient as current_tensor.gradient 
                    and input_tensors as input_tensors
                
                Note: Accumulate gradients and add inputs to stack
                For i from 0 to length of input_tensors minus 1:
                    Let input_tensor be input_tensors[i]
                    Let input_grad be input_gradients[i]
                    
                    If input_tensor.requires_grad:
                        If input_tensor.gradient is None:
                            Set input_tensor.gradient to Some with value as input_grad
                        Else:
                            Let accumulated_grad be tensor_add_arrays with 
                                array1 as input_tensor.gradient 
                                and array2 as input_grad
                            Set input_tensor.gradient to Some with value as accumulated_grad
                        
                        Add input_tensor to computation_stack
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Process called "zero_gradients" that takes tensors as List[Tensor] returns Boolean:
    Note: Zero out gradients of all tensors
    Try:
        For each tensor in tensors:
            If tensor.requires_grad:
                Set tensor.gradient to None
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Note: =============================================================================
Note: OPTIMIZERS - Advanced Parameter Update Algorithms
Note: =============================================================================

Type called "Optimizer":
    optimizer_type as String
    parameters as List[Tensor]
    learning_rate as Float
    state as Dictionary[String, Any]

Process called "create_sgd_optimizer" that takes 
    parameters as List[Tensor]
    and learning_rate as Float
    and momentum as Optional[Float]
    returns Optimizer:

    Note: Create Stochastic Gradient Descent optimizer
    Let momentum_value be momentum or 0.0
    
    Let optimizer_state be Dictionary with:
        "momentum" as momentum_value
        "velocity" as Dictionary with empty entries
    
    Return Optimizer with:
        optimizer_type as "sgd"
        parameters as parameters
        learning_rate as learning_rate
        state as optimizer_state

Process called "create_adam_optimizer" that takes 
    parameters as List[Tensor]
    and learning_rate as Optional[Float]
    and beta1 as Optional[Float]
    and beta2 as Optional[Float]
    and epsilon as Optional[Float]
    returns Optimizer:

    Note: Create Adam optimizer
    Let lr be learning_rate or 0.001
    Let b1 be beta1 or 0.9
    Let b2 be beta2 or 0.999
    Let eps be epsilon or 0.00000001
    
    Let optimizer_state be Dictionary with:
        "beta1" as b1
        "beta2" as b2
        "epsilon" as eps
        "step" as 0
        "m" as Dictionary with empty entries  Note: First moment estimates
        "v" as Dictionary with empty entries  Note: Second moment estimates
    
    Return Optimizer with:
        optimizer_type as "adam"
        parameters as parameters
        learning_rate as lr
        state as optimizer_state

Process called "optimizer_step" that takes optimizer as Optimizer returns Boolean:
    Note: Perform one optimization step
    Try:
        Match optimizer.optimizer_type:
            When "sgd":
                Let momentum be optimizer.state["momentum"] as Float
                
                For i from 0 to length of optimizer.parameters minus 1:
                    Let param be optimizer.parameters[i]
                    
                    If param.requires_grad and param.gradient is not None:
                        Let param_id be i as String
                        
                        If momentum is greater than 0.0:
                            Note: SGD with momentum
                            Let velocity_dict be optimizer.state["velocity"] as Dictionary[String, sci.NDArray]
                            
                            If not dict_ops.dictionary_contains_key with dictionary as velocity_dict and key as param_id:
                                Set velocity_dict[param_id] to sci.zeros with shape as param.data.shape and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
                            
                            Let velocity be velocity_dict[param_id]
                            
                            Note: Update velocity: v = momentum * v - lr * grad
                            Let momentum_term be scale_array with array as velocity and scale as momentum
                            Let gradient_term be scale_array with array as param.gradient and scale as optimizer.learning_rate
                            Set velocity to subtract_arrays with array1 as momentum_term and array2 as gradient_term
                            Set velocity_dict[param_id] to velocity
                            
                            Note: Update parameter: param = param + velocity
                            Set param.data to add_arrays with array1 as param.data and array2 as velocity
                        
                        Else:
                            Note: Standard SGD: param = param - lr * grad
                            Let update_term be scale_array with array as param.gradient and scale as optimizer.learning_rate
                            Set param.data to subtract_arrays with array1 as param.data and array2 as update_term
            
            When "adam":
                Let beta1 be optimizer.state["beta1"] as Float
                Let beta2 be optimizer.state["beta2"] as Float
                Let epsilon be optimizer.state["epsilon"] as Float
                Set optimizer.state["step"] to optimizer.state["step"] as Integer plus 1
                Let step be optimizer.state["step"] as Integer
                
                Let m_dict be optimizer.state["m"] as Dictionary[String, sci.NDArray]
                Let v_dict be optimizer.state["v"] as Dictionary[String, sci.NDArray]
                
                For i from 0 to length of optimizer.parameters minus 1:
                    Let param be optimizer.parameters[i]
                    
                    If param.requires_grad and param.gradient is not None:
                        Let param_id be i as String
                        
                        Note: Initialize moment estimates if needed
                        If not dict_ops.dictionary_contains_key with dictionary as m_dict and key as param_id:
                            Set m_dict[param_id] to sci.zeros with shape as param.data.shape and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
                            Set v_dict[param_id] to sci.zeros with shape as param.data.shape and dtype as Some with value as "float32"
                        
                        Let m be m_dict[param_id]
                        Let v be v_dict[param_id]
                        
                        Note: Update biased first moment estimate: m = β1 * m + (1 - β1) * grad
                        Let beta1_term be scale_array with array as m and scale as beta1
                        Let grad_term be scale_array with array as param.gradient and scale as 1.0 minus beta1
                        Set m to add_arrays with array1 as beta1_term and array2 as grad_term
                        Set m_dict[param_id] to m
                        
                        Note: Update biased second moment estimate: v = β2 * v + (1 - β2) * grad²
                        Let beta2_term be scale_array with array as v and scale as beta2
                        Let grad_squared be element_wise_multiply with array1 as param.gradient and array2 as param.gradient
                        Let grad_squared_term be scale_array with array as grad_squared and scale as 1.0 minus beta2
                        Set v to add_arrays with array1 as beta2_term and array2 as grad_squared_term
                        Set v_dict[param_id] to v
                        
                        Note: Compute bias-corrected first moment estimate
                        Let bias_correction1 be 1.0 minus math.pow with base as beta1 and exponent as step as Float
                        Let m_corrected be scale_array with array as m and scale as 1.0 divided by bias_correction1
                        
                        Note: Compute bias-corrected second moment estimate
                        Let bias_correction2 be 1.0 minus math.pow with base as beta2 and exponent as step as Float
                        Let v_corrected be scale_array with array as v and scale as 1.0 divided by bias_correction2
                        
                        Note: Update parameter: param = param - lr * m_corrected / (sqrt(v_corrected) + ε)
                        Let v_sqrt be element_wise_sqrt with array as v_corrected
                        Let denominator be add_scalar_to_array with array as v_sqrt and scalar as epsilon
                        Let update_direction be element_wise_divide with array1 as m_corrected and array2 as denominator
                        Let update_term be scale_array with array as update_direction and scale as optimizer.learning_rate
                        Set param.data to subtract_arrays with array1 as param.data and array2 as update_term
            
            Default:
                Return false
        
        Return true
    
    Catch error:
        Return false

Note: =============================================================================
Note: TRAINING UTILITIES - Model Training Infrastructure
Note: =============================================================================

Type called "TrainingResult":
    epoch_losses as List[Float]
    final_loss as Float
    training_time as Float
    converged as Boolean

Process called "train_model" that takes 
    model as NeuralNetwork
    and train_data as List[Tensor]
    and train_targets as List[Tensor]
    and optimizer as Optimizer
    and loss_function as String
    and epochs as Integer
    and batch_size as Optional[Integer]
    returns TrainingResult:

    Note: Train neural network model
    Try:
        Let batch_sz be batch_size or 32
        Let epoch_losses be empty list
        Let start_time be get_current_time
        
        For epoch from 0 to epochs minus 1:
            Let epoch_loss be 0.0
            Let num_batches be 0
            
            Note: Process data in batches
            For batch_start from 0 to length of train_data step batch_sz:
                Let batch_end be math.min with value1 as batch_start plus batch_sz and value2 as length of train_data
                
                Note: Zero gradients
                Let zero_grad_success be zero_gradients with tensors as model.parameters
                
                Let batch_loss be 0.0
                
                Note: Process batch
                For i from batch_start to batch_end minus 1:
                    Let input_tensor be train_data[i]
                    Let target_tensor be train_targets[i]
                    
                    Note: Forward pass
                    Let forward_result be neural_network_forward with network as model and input_tensor as input_tensor
                    
                    Match forward_result:
                        When success as true and tensor as Some with value as prediction:
                            Note: Compute loss
                            Let loss_result be compute_loss with 
                                loss_type as loss_function 
                                and predictions as prediction 
                                and targets as target_tensor
                            
                            Match loss_result:
                                When success as true and tensor as Some with value as loss_tensor:
                                    Set batch_loss to batch_loss plus get_scalar_value with tensor as loss_tensor
                                    
                                    Note: Backward pass
                                    Let backward_success be backward with loss_tensor as loss_tensor
                                
                                Default:
                                    Continue  Note: Skip failed loss computation
                        
                        Default:
                            Continue  Note: Skip failed forward pass
                
                Note: Optimizer step
                Let step_success be optimizer_step with optimizer as optimizer
                
                Set epoch_loss to epoch_loss plus batch_loss divided by batch_end minus batch_start as Float
                Set num_batches to num_batches plus 1
            
            Let avg_epoch_loss be epoch_loss divided by num_batches as Float
            Add avg_epoch_loss to epoch_losses
        
        Let end_time be get_current_time
        Let training_time be end_time minus start_time
        
        Let final_loss be epoch_losses[length of epoch_losses minus 1]
        Let converged be final_loss is less than 0.001  Note: Simple convergence criterion
        
        Return TrainingResult with:
            epoch_losses as epoch_losses
            final_loss as final_loss
            training_time as training_time
            converged as converged
    
    Catch error:
        Return TrainingResult with:
            epoch_losses as empty list
            final_loss as 999999.0
            training_time as 0.0
            converged as false

Note: =============================================================================
Note: HELPER FUNCTIONS - Internal Implementation Support
Note: =============================================================================

Process called "tensors_same_shape" that takes t1 as Tensor and t2 as Tensor returns Boolean:
    Note: Check if two tensors have the same shape
    If length of t1.data.shape is not equal to length of t2.data.shape:
        Return false
    
    For i from 0 to length of t1.data.shape minus 1:
        If t1.data.shape[i] is not equal to t2.data.shape[i]:
            Return false
    
    Return true

Process called "generate_random_uniform" that takes seed as Integer returns Float:
    Note: Generate pseudo-random uniform value between 0 and 1
    Let a be 1664525
    Let c be 1013904223
    Let m be 4294967296  Note: 2^32
    
    Let random_val be a multiplied by seed plus c modulo m
    Return random_val as Float divided by m as Float

Process called "scale_tensor" that takes tensor as Tensor and scale_factor as Float returns Tensor:
    Note: Scale tensor by constant factor
    Let scaled_data be empty list
    
    For i from 0 to tensor.data.size minus 1:
        Let scaled_val be tensor.data.data[i] as Float multiplied by scale_factor
        Add scaled_val to scaled_data
    
    Let scaled_array be sci.create_ndarray with 
        data as scaled_data 
        and shape as Some with value as tensor.data.shape 
        and dtype as Some with value as tensor.data.dtype
    
    Match scaled_array:
        When success as true and array as Some with value as result_array:
            Return Tensor with:
                data as result_array
                requires_grad as tensor.requires_grad
                gradient as None
                computation_graph as None
                device as tensor.device
        Default:
            Return tensor

Process called "tensor_transpose" that takes tensor as Tensor returns TensorResult:
    Note: Transpose tensor (reverse last two dimensions)
    Let transpose_result be sci.transpose with array as tensor.data
    
    Match transpose_result:
        When success as true and array as Some with value as transposed_array:
            Return TensorResult with:
                success as true
                tensor as Some with value as Tensor with:
                    data as transposed_array
                    requires_grad as tensor.requires_grad
                    gradient as None
                    computation_graph as None
                    device as tensor.device
        Default:
            Return TensorResult with:
                success as false
                error_message as Some with value as "Tensor transpose failed"

Process called "get_current_time" returns Float:
    Note: Get current timestamp (simplified implementation)
    Return 1000.0  Note: Would return actual timestamp in real implementation

Process called "get_scalar_value" that takes tensor as Tensor returns Float:
    Note: Extract scalar value from tensor
    If tensor.data.size is equal to 1:
        Return tensor.data.data[0] as Float
    Else:
        Return 0.0  Note: Default for non-scalar tensors

Process called "compute_loss" that takes 
    loss_type as String
    and predictions as Tensor
    and targets as Tensor
    returns TensorResult:

    Note: Compute loss based on specified type
    Match loss_type:
        When "mse":
            Return mean_squared_error_loss with predictions as predictions and targets as targets
        
        When "cross_entropy":
            Return cross_entropy_loss with predictions as predictions and targets as targets
        
        Default:
            Return TensorResult with:
                success as false
                error_message as Some with value as "Unknown loss function: " plus loss_type